This powerful non-bleach toilet cleaner deodorizes as it dissolves dirt and grime. Get complete coverage and complete clean with Clorox Toilet Bowl Cleaner Tough Stain Remover.


Directions: To open, squeeze sides of cap where symbols indicate and twist counterclockwise one-quarter turn. Cap does not come off. To reseal, turn cap clockwise until tightly closed. Warnings: This toilet cleaner causes substantial but temporary eye injury. Do not get in eyes, on skin or clothing. Wear protective eyewear. Do not use or mix with products that contain bleach (sodium hypochlorite). To do so may release hazardous gases. Always flush toilet before and after use of this product.

Usage Directions: To open, squeeze sides of cap where symbols indicate and twist counterclockwise one-quarter turn. Cap does not come off. To reseal, turn cap clockwise until tightly closed. Scrub the entire bowl with a stiff brush and allow to sit for 10 minutes to disinfect. Do not allow pets or children to access the toilet during this time. Flush toilet.

Ingredients: Sodium Hypochlorite 2.4%. Other ingredients: 97.6%.

Warnings: Causes irreversible eye damage. Causes skin irritation. Prolonged or frequently repeated skin contact may cause allergic reactions in some individuals. Do not get toilet cleaner in eyes, on skin or on clothing. For prolonged use, wear gloves. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling. Remove and wash contaminated clothing before reuse. Use only in well-ventilated areas. Keep out of reach of children. Hazardous to humans and domestic animals.

It also removes mold and mildew stains with less scrubbing, so it is perfect for freshening and cleaning tubs, tile, toilets, sinks and counters. The Smart Tube technology insures you spray every stain fighting drop. Behind every sparkling clean bathroom, there is Clorox Bleach Foamer Bathroom Spray.


Usage Directions: To Clean Soap Scum: Spray, wait a few minutes, wipe with sponge. Heavy soap scum or mildew buildup may need two cleanings. To Disinfect and Kill Mold & Mildew on Hard, Nonporous Surfaces such as glazed ceramic tile: Spray surface until thoroughly wet, let stand 5 minutes, and rinse. To Remove Mildew Stains: Spray 68 inches from surface until surface is thoroughly covered. Allow foam to deeply penetrate mildew and problem areas. Wipe with a wet sponge or cloth, and rinse. Heavy mildew buildup may require longer contact time, or two cleanings.

Ingredients: Sodium hypochlorite, 2.40%; other ingredients, 97.60%. Contains no phosphorus.

Warnings: Not recommended for use by persons with heart conditions or chronic respiratory problems such as asthma, emphysema or lung disease. FIRST AID: IF IN EYES: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 1520 minutes. Remove contact lenses. IF INHALED: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration. IF SWALLOWED: Call a poison control center immediately for treatment advice. PHYSICAL AND CHEMICAL HAZARDS: This product contains bleach. Do not use or mix this product with other chemicals containing ammonia.

description:
Kills Bugs Dead. Raid Roach Gel is an easy way to apply bait, killing all common household roaches at the source. This indoor ready-to-use gel bait starts working in hours as a crack and crevice treatment in areas such as kitchens, bathrooms, laundry rooms, basements, and garages.

DIRECTIONS FOR USE: It is a violation of Federal law to use this product in a manner inconsistent with its labeling. READ THIS LABEL: Read this entire label and follow all use directions and use precautions. Use only for the sites, pests, and application methods described on this label. BACKGROUND INFORMATION: Raid Roach Gel is a ready-to-use highly attractive gel bait formulation that is very effective in controlling German and American cockroaches. BEFORE YOU START: Apply to areas not easily accessible to children and pets. Do not apply Raid Roach Gel bait to surfaces recently treated with residual insecticide sprays. Surfaces treated with Raid Roach Gel bait must not be treated with insecticidal sprays, as the bait will be rendered ineffective. Do not apply in or on electrical equipment due to the possibility of shock. Do not apply to surfaces that food contacts. Do not allow open foods to contact gel material. Do not apply in locations of high temperature or direct sunlight. Gel deposits may be cleaned up by using damp paper towel or rag while still wet, or if dried, use putty knife to scrape and discard in trash. May be used indoors as a crack and crevice treatment in and around single and multi-family residential buildings. Apply to areas roaches are commonly found, such as: Under sinks and around plumbing and pipes; to drawers and cabinet corners where roaches are known to hide; equipment legs and bases and behind and under appliances such as ovens, refrigerators, and washers; openings leading into cracks, and hollow spaces in floors, walls, and ceilings; trashcans; behind toilets; baseboards, doors and windows. Do not apply in locations of high temperature or direct sunlight. Inspect bait placements periodically and apply fresh bait as needed. HOW TO APPLY 1. Remove cap to open. 2. Place tube tip at surface to be treated. 3. Gently squeeze tube to create multiple spots of gel about the size of a pea, or apply as a line or strip. When finished, lift tube tip from surface, and replace cap to close. 4. Keep the cap on the tube to prevent gel from drying out. HOW MUCH TO APPLY For spot or gel dot applications: For heavy infestations of roaches, apply 3 to 5 spots of Raid Roach Gel bait per 10 linear feet or one square yard. For light to moderate infestations of roaches, apply 1 - 3 spots of Raid Roach Gel bait per 10 linear feet or one square yard. Each gel dot of Raid Roach Gel applied should be about the size of a pea. To apply a line of gel: For all levels of roach infestations, when a line of Raid Roach Gel bait is used, apply a small thin strip that is less than 1/8 inches wide and approximately 2 inches long. Inspect bait placements periodically and reapply fresh bait as needed.

USES: Use in hard to reach places like cracks and crevices, in corners, along walls, and near entry points to kill roaches where they hide. Kills: Cockroaches (including German and American) Where to use: In and around homes and other buildings/structures where cockroaches have infested or where they travel to seek food, water or shelter. When to use: When cockroaches are observed or there is evidence of an infestation in/around a home, building or structure.
title: Raid Roach Gel, 1.5oz

description:
Clorox Scentiva Multi Surface Cleaner cleans and kills 99.9% of viruses and bacteria throughout your home, leaving behind a fabulous Hawaiian Sunshine. This intense scented, all-purpose cleaner is bleach-free and has no chemical scent at all. Use this all purpose cleaner for garbage cans, kitchen countertops, sinks, and appliances. This all purpose cleaner powers through grease and grime with ease. It is also the ideal bathroom cleaner that cleans toilets, tubs, cabinets and floors. Utilize this all purpose cleaner to cut down on your necessary cleaning supplies and quickly spray away an array of messes. This all purpose cleaner is safe to use on most surfaces and around pet areas. Clorox Scentiva disinfectant spray cleaner eliminates 99.9% of germs while cleaning your entire home to a sparkle. With sensational smelling Scentiva, you'll want your whole house to smell like this.


Directions: Spray 6 to 8 inches from surface. Spray product straight onto soils and wipe clean with a dry paper towel or lint free cloth. Repeat for heavily soiled areas. Refill only with this product. To Disinfect: Spray until thoroughly wet. Let stand 10 minutes, then wipe. For heavily soiled areas, precleaning is required. All surfaces that come in contact with food must be rinsed with potable water. Do not use on glasses, dishes or utensils. Not recommended for use on soft vinyl, varnishes or aluminum.

Ingredients: Active Ingredient: Alkyl (C12 40%; C14 50%; C16 10%), dimethyl benzyl ammonium chloride .3%, other ingredients 99.7%.

Warnings: Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes, skin, clothing or foods. Wash with soap and water after handling. If in eyes: Hold eye open and rise slowly with water for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after 5 minutes, then continue rising eye. If on skin or clothing: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin with plenty of water for 15 to 20 minutes. Have product container with you when calling a poison control center or doctor, or going for treatment.

description:
Clorox UltimateCare Bleach whitens and cleans with a pleasant scent. This user friendly bleach not only has a gentle soft cotton scent, but also works gently on even delicate laundry. The thick no splash formulated bleach can be poured directly onto fabrics to pretreat tough stains. With no overpowering bleach odor, the proof of the bleaching power can be seen in the whitening results. This bleach can be used in standard and high efficiency washing machines. Clorox UltimateCare Gentle Bleach offers a gentle Soft Cotton scent.

Usage Directions: Sort laundry by color. Add detergent and laundry to wash water. Add Clorox UltimateCare Bleach. To pretreat stains, remove any loose soil, apply bleach directly to stain, rub in and let sit 3 minutes. Add rest of capful to washer and wash immediately. This bleach is safe for most whites. If in doubt, apply one drop to hidden area. Rinse after 3 minutes, blot dry. If no color change, garment can be safely bleached. Avoid bleaching wool, silk, mohair, leather, spandex and nonfast colors.

Caution Statements: Eye and skin irritant. Avoid contact with eyes. For sensitive skin or prolonged use, wear rubber gloves. Use with adequate ventilation. If contact with eyes occurs, immediately rinse with water for 15 minutes. Call a doctor. If contact with skin occurs, rinse with water. If irritation persists, call a doctor. If swallowed, drink a glass of water. Call a doctor or poison control center. Keep out of reach of children. Do not use or mix with other chemicals as hazardous gases may result.
title: Clorox UltimateCare Bleach, Soft Cotton Scent, 30 oz

bullets: Clorox UltimateCare Bleach Whitens and Clean Delicate Laundry
Soft cotton scent
Thicker, no splash formula

description:
Combine the cleaning power of Clorox Performance Bleach with CloroMax technology, this number one bleach of choice in America now keeps clothes whiter longer based on stain removal verses detergent alone and cleans and protects surfaces by reducing soil adhesion while leaving a pleasant Fresh Meadow fragrance. This concentrated formula, filtered three times to deliver the purest bleach, removes 70% more stains than detergents alone and protects surfaces for easier, reduced cleaning effort. Use Clorox Bleach with CloroMax technology with confidence to remove tough laundry stains like grass, juice, dirt and blood from white clothing to cleaning countertops, floors, sinks, and trash cans. This sodium hypochlorite bleach can be used in standard and high efficiency washing machines. Great for everyday cleaning and seasonal cleaning needs including Spring Cleaning, & Back to School season. Clorox Bleach with CloroMax technology cleans, protects and deodorizes to keep your laundry and home smelling fresh.

Usage Directions: For laundry, sort laundry by color and add detergent. Fill bleach to max line in dispenser or add 1/2 cup bleach to wash water. Add clothes and start wash. For best results, add to wash 5 minutes after the wash cycle has begun. For cleaning and deodorizing, dilute 1/2 cup of bleach with 1 gallon of water. Pre-wash surface, mop or wipe with bleach solution. Allow solution to contact surface for at least 5 minutes. Rinse well and air dry. For prolonged use, wear rubber gloves.

Caution Statements: Eye and skin irritant. Avoid contact with eyes. For sensitive skin or prolonged use, wear rubber gloves. Use with adequate ventilation. If contact with eyes occurs, immediately rinse with water for 15 minutes. Call a doctor. If contact with skin occurs, rinse with water. If irritation persists, call a doctor. If swallowed, drink a glass of water. Call a doctor or poison control center. Keep out of reach of children. Do not use or mix with other household chemicals as hazardous gases may result.
